      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INTERRO (8) is the threat. Opened this preparation with a comfortable Maiden win at Goulburn and then raced a little flat in stronger than this at Newcastle. Fitter again, and the longer sprint is sure to suit. Collett strikes at 20% this venue, and she's a positive jockey engagement. FACEOFF (3) had been threatening a win at the provincials and prepared to forgive his latest effort in a 66 on an iffy surface at Goulburn. Draws well enough, and the blinkers are applied for the first time. Keep safe. COMMON GOAL (6) won a Queanbeyan Maiden two back as expected, and his Newcastle finishes each side of that stack up. Drops back 200m but races on pace and is sure to be strong to the line. WALK THE PIER (4) resumes and has the inside gate and Penz aboard. Has good ability and has to be considered as well.",
